title: Fix a bug where the native code wouldn't get the whole framebuffer on Tegra 2.
message:
Fix a bug where the native code wouldn't get the whole framebuffer on Tegra 2.

fbread apparently wasn't producing data fast enough, so read was returning after
around 2000 bytes. It now attempts read() in a loop until it gets enough bytes,
EOF, or an error.

screenshots for a single shake of the phone are much less likely.

title: Add android.util.Base64 from the Gingerbread source. Target API lvl 7.

Add android.util.Base64 from the Gingerbread source. Target API lvl 7.

Base64 wasn't introduced until API lvl 8, so just copying the one class makes it
possible to target lvl 7 and possibly lower.
